           <p>
               This website, named Web2, was started in the Summer of 2018, and completed in the Fall of 2018.
               Web2 was my initiative to learn to make a functional and presentable website from scratch.
               The vision for this website was to be a place for me to share my projects easily.
               Using HTML, CSS, and JS, along with help from online tutorials, I managed to achieve just that.
               </br></br>
               A Raspberry Pi 3 B+ was used to host the website due to it's low cost, small size, low power usage, and relatively good computing power.
               Apache was chosen as the HTTP server due to it's simplicity to use.
               Below shows a size comparison of my Raspberry Pi and a credit card.
               </br></br>
               <p style="text-align:center;"><img id="RPImage" src="/media/web2/RPI.jpg" style="width:756px;height:567px;"><p>
               </br>
               The website name needed to reflect the personal nature of this website; so the domain www.shykowski.ca was chosen.
               A subdomain was created to further this personalization: hudson.shykowski.ca.
               You can visit either of the URLs, but you will be redirected to the second one.
               </br></br>
               The following free online resources made this website possible:
               <ul>
                   <li><a class="desclink" target="_blank" href="https://vincentgarreau.com/particles.js/">Particles.js</a> - a particle simulation JavaScript library</li>
                   <li><a class="desclink" target="_blank" href="https://jquery.com">JQuery</a> - a JavaScript library that simplifies many web-actions</li>
                   <li><a class="desclink" target="_blank" href="https://jqueryui.com">JQuery UI</a> - a JavaScript library that simplifies animation processes</li>
                   <li><a class="desclink" target="_blank" href="https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/">A Complete Guide to Flexbox</a> - A Flexbox CSS guide</li>
                   <li><a class="desclink" target="_blank" href="https://smallenvelop.com/display-loading-icon-page-loads-completely/">Guide</a> to displaying a loading icon until a webpage completely loads</li>
                   <li><a class="desclink" target="_blank" href="https://www.w3schools.com">W3schools.com</a> - A website containing HTML, CSS, and JS guides</li>
               </ul>
           </p>
